<h2>Magnetic fields</h2>
<div class="container">
  <div class="info-card">
    <h2>Fundamental nature of magnetism</h2>
    <p>
      The fundamental nature of magnetism is the interaction of moving electric charges.<br>
      Like Electric forces, Magnetic forces also arise in two stages.
      <ul>
        <li>First, a moving charge or a collection of moving charges (that is, an electric current) produces a magnetic field.</li>
        <li>Next, a second current or moving charge responds to this magnetic field, and so experiences a magnetic force.</li>
      </ul>
      We are dealing with the first question now. For the second, see "Motor".
    </p>


